@scottpurdy The MS Visual C build system uses file extensions to determine whether to invoke the C++ pre-processor. The `/TP` flag is a way to force that invocation. A similar flag `/TC` is used to enforce that a source file only contains C code.
The `/TP` flag can be used, for instance, if someone added a source file with a '.c' extension, but used C++ within the file. At the moment that case doesn't existing within NuPIC.Core
It's debatable as to whether to keep the '/TP' flag at all, and just rely on making sure that any further code files added adhere to the correct file extension (i.e. `.cpp` or `.cxx`, vs `.c`), something fairly obvious to most developers.

