@rueberger I've been dealing with this same issue since getting up and running last week and am more or less dealing with similar things.  The only other workaround I've come up with is similar to #211 - decorate `generate_foo_config` with `@experiment.config` and then delete any variables you don't want tagged onto the config.  Something like this:

```
@experiment.config
def generate_foo_config(*args, **kwargs): 
    intermediate_variable = some_other_fn(args[2])
    arg_for_config = another_fn(intermediate_variable)
    del intermediate_variable
```

Also, if you're nesting configurations, I highly recommend using `Ingredients`.  Based on your code, it seems like you could have one for `data`, `train`, and `model`.  Just cross your fingers there aren't any dependencies among them or it gets hairy quickly.  It'd be a lot nicer with the OO approach we mentioned in #193, but I haven't had a chance to get going on that yet.

