For using unions as connections, you need to create a ConnectionType for the union.
The following should work:

```python
class Cat(graphene.ObjectType):
    class Meta:
        interfaces = (relay.Node,)
    name = graphene.String()

class Dog(graphene.ObjectType):
    class Meta:
        interfaces = (relay.Node,)
    name = graphene.String()

class Animal(Union):
    class Meta:
        types = (Cat, Dog)

class AnimalConnection(graphene.Connection):
    class Meta:
        node = Animal

class Query(graphene.ObjectType):
    animals = graphene.ConnectionField(AnimalConnection)
```

(related issue #356)

