I replicated the code for the similar BVLC filter and have confirmed my proposed method is the same.

https://github.com/tnarihi/caffe/commit/4f249a00a29432e0bb6723087ec64187e1506f0f

```
filt = np.zeros([2,1,8,8])
filt2 = np.reshape(filt,[-1])
width,height=(8,8)
f = math.ceil(width / 2.);
c = (2 * f - 1 - f % 2) / (2. * f);
for i in range(len(filt2)):
    x = i %width
    y = (i / width)% height;
    filt2[i] = (1 - abs(x / f - c)) * (1 - abs(y / f - c));
filt3=np.reshape(filt2,[2,1,8,8])
filt3[0][0].shape
```

